<title>UK: UK abolishes div tax credits to pension funds/cos.</title>
<headline>UK abolishes div tax credits to pension funds/cos.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>UK Chancellor Gordon Brown said on Wednesday that tax credits paid to pension funds and companies would be abolished with immediate effect.  </p>
<p>Brown also said that higher rate tax payers would pay no more tax on dividends than they do now.</p>
<p>In a bid to encourage savings, the government is also introducing individual savings accounts from 1999 and Brown added that the budget would not phase out tax relief on employee pension contributions.</p>
